20 May 2008Minister of Safety and Security Mr Charles Nqakula together with other Justice Crime Prevention and Security (JCPS) cluster Ministers will visit Ekhuruleni today, where there has been a spate of xenophobic attacks.Media are invited to gather at Primrose Police Station at 11h00.The event will take place as follows:Date: 20 May 2008 Time: 11h00 Venue: Primrose Police StationEnquiries Hangwani Mulaudzi Cell: 082 555 3505Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)